Edition: (1889,1974)
Quote: NOTE. - As I have no desire to mystify readers unacquainted with New Zealand flora, I append a brief description of the shrubs mentioned:- <i> Kowhai </i>  - A papilonaceous flowering tree, of the <i> acacia </i>  tribe. [17] <i> Bush-lawyer </i> - Native name, Tataramoa - A disagreeable bramble, very tenacious of grasp. <i> Koromiko </i>  - A white flowering Veronica. <i> Tutu </i>  - A berry-bearing, glossy-leaved plant, deadly to man and to all animals - except goats. <i> Tumata-kuru </i>  - Better known as `Wild Irishman' - a thorny plant, very difficult to handle.
