Date: 0/0/1958
Source: Whitcombe's Modern Junior Dictionary (8th edn)
Author:
Vol / Page: 224
Edition:
Quote: <i>  Irishman, wild </i>  A common New Zealand shrub of the buckthorn family, also called `matagouri' (<i> ma|-ta-go|-ry </i> ). The real Maori name is `tumata-kuru', of which `matagouri' is an incorrect form.
Notes:

